<div class="center"><br />Inspiration: Paul Frederick's work tempts me to buy <em>very</em> expensive toys</div>
<p>Sean, Greg, and I seized the day this afternoon.  Conditions were ideal for a cycling sojourn. The air was dry and the sun's rays warm, but ambient coolness hid in the shadows.</p>
<p>Turret, iSean's snazzy new Felt Bike, has him flying uphill. Now all he has to do is eat <em>before</em> riding.</p>
<p>And ascending isn't his only talent. He goes downhill FAST!</p>
<p>Indeed, he kept Greg company on their blistering descent. I made my way down in the prop wash. But that's fine: the views were spectacular.</p>